Italy Credit-Default Swaps Rise 35 Basis Points to Record 282

-- B y   A b i g a i l   M o s e s
-- 
2011-07-11T08:09:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-11/italy-credit-default-swaps-rise-35-basis-points-to-record-282.html
The cost of insuring Italian
sovereign debt jumped 35 basis points to 282 basis points,
according to BNP Parisbas SA prices for credit-default swaps.
That exceeds the previous closing record of 271 basis points on
Nov. 30, according to CMA.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Abigail Moses in London at 
